rComments: If you want an easyA to up you GPA, then take one of his classes. If you are seeking a professional, trustworthy, academic who is reachable and meaningfully responds to feedback requests and/or any recommendations based on high performance then do not hold your breath. This guy is unavailable and an irresponsible academic ... #deadwood

He is the best of the best. I have never seen such a knowledgeable professor. He is a master in his job. Also, he is a  very kind and considerate human being. I will take all of his courses. He is the BEST.
Interesting professor. Is often late or unprepared for class but is of great help when you are willing to understand the topics. He grades very generously and is a great seminar professor.
The best professor I have ever had. A good human being, and very well-read. His knowledge of theory is amazing.

He is an extremely intelligent professor who is willing to challenge his students and their beliefs. His classes can be slightly boring, however, this is because of his greater emphasis on being a moderator for discussion rather, than lecturing. He encourages his students to explore new theoretical tropes and provides guidance when needed.
Really interesting prof, he knows his stuff but he's very disorganized. His lectures are fairly interesting though.

He had almost no control over his class. He got off topic all the time and going to his class was an incredible waste of time. He didn't explain anything clearly and made promises to the class that he did not end up keeping.

Dr. Tavakoli is one of the nicest prof's at UoFT he is really funny and flamboyant, his marking scheme is pretty easy, and he is not afraid do give out good marks, but he is very unorganized, and he is almost impossible to find. The many is simply involved in way too many things at the same time. Overall, he is a good prof.
